verses.roman:
eta bali' mahāprabhu bhakta-gaṇa-saṅge
cali' āilā brahmānanda-bhāratīra āge

synonyms: eta bali'-saying this; mahāprabhu—Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu; bhakta-gaṇa-saṅge—with the devotees; cali'—walking; āilā—came; brahmānanda-bhāratīra—of Brahmānanda Bhāratī; āge—in the presence.
translation: After saying this, Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu and His devotees came into the presence of Brahmānanda Bhāratī.
